  "curation": {
    "synopsis": "Cain's long-deferred retirement is on the line again when Astra Militarum weapon shipments from the newly founded forge world of Ironfound dry up overnight. Sent in nominally as a Commissariat liaison, Cain — with Jurgen at his side and Amberley Vail running parallel Inquisitorial cover — uncovers a tangle of mutinous Skitarii, doctrinal heresy inside the Adeptus Mechanicus magos hierarchy, and a string of insidious assassination attempts that get more personal the deeper he digs. The hidden hand behind it pulls strings inside Ironfound's own Fabricator-General circle, with an agenda that threatens Imperial control of the Damocles Gulf and chains back to the Drechia conspiracy in Choose Your Enemies. Cain emerges nominally a hero, definitely alive, and slightly closer to the retirement that will never come.",
